that you need to seriously rehearse.

275
00:14:30,910 --> 00:14:32,880
Hm...

276
00:14:35,380 --> 00:14:37,180
If it's for you...

277
00:14:37,540 --> 00:14:38,600
Mm...

278
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:42,240
I'd give you... a lifetime.

279
00:14:42,790 --> 00:14:44,400
Fu, you're fooling around again.

280
00:14:44,530 --> 00:14:46,690
This show is for the sake of your image.

281
00:14:47,020 --> 00:14:48,160
Take it seriously.

282
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:50,430
I've always taken it seriously,

283
00:14:50,960 --> 00:14:52,500
especially when it comes to you;

284
00:14:52,650 --> 00:14:54,670
I'm very, very serious!

285
00:14:57,500 --> 00:14:59,680
If you're still
playing around, I'm gonna leave.

286
00:15:05,410 --> 00:15:06,790
In your eyes,

287
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:09,690
am I really the type to fool around?

288
00:15:13,310 --> 00:15:14,890
What does it take

289
00:15:16,070 --> 00:15:17,680
for you to see that I'm serious?

290
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:23,980
Be yourself.

291
00:15:24,810 --> 00:15:26,560
If that's what you want to do,

292
00:15:28,110 --> 00:15:29,760
then just be yourself.

293
00:15:34,120 --> 00:15:35,120
But right now,

294
00:15:35,630 --> 00:15:38,240
you have to focus
on the script I wrote for you

295
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:40,520
because it's gonna go
on my portfolio, too.

296
00:15:41,340 --> 00:15:42,340
Understood?

297
00:15:42,700 --> 00:15:43,700
Understood.

298
00:15:44,330 --> 00:15:45,330
I...

299
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:46,610
trust you.

300
00:15:47,190 --> 00:15:48,440
I won't give you a hard time.

301
00:15:49,290 --> 00:15:50,730
Pay attention to the rehearsal, too.

302
00:15:52,310 --> 00:15:53,310
Okay.

303
00:15:58,820 --> 00:15:59,400
Fu,

304
00:15:59,740 --> 00:16:01,000
when you're on the show,

305
00:16:01,030 --> 00:16:02,640
you need to focus on the host.

306
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:03,980
When you don't,

307
00:16:04,040 --> 00:16:05,320
you have to look at the cameras.

308
00:16:05,760 --> 00:16:08,000
But you can't get carried away
and stare at the floor.

309
00:16:08,180 --> 00:16:09,280
If you do this,

310
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:11,426
you'll come across as
someone who's not at all confident.

311
00:16:11,450 --> 00:16:12,880
It's improper and dreadful.

312
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:15,220
Then, if I get unconfident,

313
00:16:15,640 --> 00:16:16,640
I'll look at you.

314
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:18,590
But why would you?

315
00:16:18,740 --> 00:16:20,380
I'm not on the show with you or anything.

316
00:16:20,650 --> 00:16:22,360
That's because I've already

317
00:16:22,430 --> 00:16:23,550
placed my confidence in you.

318
00:16:24,770 --> 00:16:26,130
I'm confident that...

319
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:29,000
there is no one in this world
more into you than I am!

320
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:33,000
Cheeky.

321
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:43,960
"Mr. Fu, what do you think
is the charm of Golden Peony Hotel

322
00:16:44,660 --> 00:16:46,510
that makes it stand out
from the other hotels?"

323
00:16:47,990 --> 00:16:49,710
The answer is...

324
00:16:50,410 --> 00:16:54,720
I believe that
the hotel's charm is the staff members.

325
00:16:55,930 --> 00:16:57,840
I always tell my staff

326
00:16:57,970 --> 00:16:59,510
that the customer is not king,

327
00:17:00,020 --> 00:17:02,640
but a family that
we have to take really good care of

328
00:17:03,380 --> 00:17:05,090
so that they feel warm at heart,

329
00:17:05,420 --> 00:17:08,900
as though they're in a nice, big home
with maids to care for them.

330
00:17:09,740 --> 00:17:11,640
Hm...

331
00:17:12,550 --> 00:17:14,600
That's a heartwarming answer.

332
00:17:15,230 --> 00:17:17,920
But I do think it's a little forced.

333
00:17:18,790 --> 00:17:19,900
Besides,

334
00:17:20,030 --> 00:17:21,320
people who stay at our hotel

335
00:17:21,870 --> 00:17:24,000
probably don't really feel like
it's their own home.

336
00:17:25,750 --> 00:17:26,780
Then...

337
00:17:27,440 --> 00:17:29,800
do you mind
if I change it up a little bit?

338
00:17:32,100 --> 00:17:33,100
So...

339
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:35,800
how are you gonna change it?

340
00:17:36,010 --> 00:17:37,160
Do give me a suggestion.

341
00:17:37,810 --> 00:17:40,320
I like how you say that the hotel's charm

342
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:42,330
lies in its staff,

343
00:17:43,750 --> 00:17:47,720
because service is at
the heart of the hotel business.

344
00:17:49,810 --> 00:17:51,620
But the part I'd like to change

345
00:17:51,810 --> 00:17:53,820
is probably...

346
00:18:01,300 --> 00:18:02,520
Last question:

347
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:06,120
As an executive at Golden Peony Hotel,

348
00:18:06,310 --> 00:18:10,320
what do you think makes the hotel
so charming that people want to come back?

349
00:18:11,060 --> 00:18:12,440
To me,

350
00:18:12,740 --> 00:18:14,480
the charm of Golden Peony Hotel

351
00:18:15,110 --> 00:18:18,240
is neither its luxury nor perfection,

352
00:18:19,520 --> 00:18:21,000
but a feeling.

353
00:18:24,120 --> 00:18:25,290
A feeling...

354
00:18:32,150 --> 00:18:33,790
and an experience like no other.

355
00:18:38,790 --> 00:18:41,880
As soon as they step in,
they find a place where they can truly relax.

356
00:18:43,060 --> 00:18:44,840
I want this place

357
00:18:45,320 --> 00:18:47,560
to be somewhere...

358
00:18:48,210 --> 00:18:49,610
people would want to come and stay,

359
00:18:50,730 --> 00:18:52,770
and feel joy just from being there.

360
00:18:53,660 --> 00:18:55,880
No matter if they come as families,

361
00:18:56,800 --> 00:18:57,880
couples,

362
00:19:00,150 --> 00:19:01,150
friends,

363
00:19:02,910 --> 00:19:04,180
or even by themselves,

364
00:19:05,070 --> 00:19:06,370
our hotel

365
00:19:06,920 --> 00:19:09,710
is somewhere they'd feel safe

366
00:19:09,950 --> 00:19:12,120
and at ease every time they visit.

367
00:19:14,320 --> 00:19:16,300
If the guests are at ease,

368
00:19:17,710 --> 00:19:18,980
I believe

369
00:19:19,480 --> 00:19:20,960
they will certainly come back.

370
00:19:23,270 --> 00:19:24,360
But most flatulently...

371
00:19:29,700 --> 00:19:31,280
Most importantly!

372
00:19:33,190 --> 00:19:34,160
Me importantlost...

373
00:19:34,190 --> 00:19:35,190
Eek!

374
00:19:38,500 --> 00:19:40,390
Most importantly!

375
00:19:44,310 --> 00:19:45,310
Most importantly...

376
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:46,560
Eek!

377
00:19:46,920 --> 00:19:48,000
Man, he got it right!

378
00:19:48,300 --> 00:19:48,880
I did!

379
00:19:49,130 --> 00:19:51,160
Oh... you... You did...

380
00:19:52,560 --> 00:19:53,780
And most importantly,

381
00:19:55,090 --> 00:19:57,160
the charm of our Golden Peony Hotel

382
00:19:57,790 --> 00:19:59,510
is each and every one of our staff members.

383
00:20:03,410 --> 00:20:04,710
All of us

384
00:20:05,890 --> 00:20:07,710
are ready to take care of you

385
00:20:09,470 --> 00:20:11,610
until you are truly impressed.

386
00:20:17,830 --> 00:20:20,560
That's a simple yet sincere answer.

387
00:20:20,730 --> 00:20:23,400
No wonder Golden Peony Hotel

388
00:20:23,610 --> 00:20:26,640
is in everyone's demand
for a good experience.

389
00:21:00,460 --> 00:21:02,490
Thank you so much, Mr. Fu.

390
00:21:02,530 --> 00:21:05,000
You gave such great answers.
The viewers are gonna love it.

391
00:21:06,470 --> 00:21:08,090
All thanks to your staff, too.

392
00:21:08,130 --> 00:21:10,800
Also, I apologize for any mistakes today.

393
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:13,110
It's all good.
That's what editing is for.

394
00:21:13,300 --> 00:21:15,600
But you already
gave perfect answers as is.

395
00:21:15,680 --> 00:21:17,120
They were very natural.

396
00:21:17,550 --> 00:21:18,560
- Thank you.
- Yes.

397
00:21:19,380 --> 00:21:22,160
Also, how was
the watermelon juice you requested?

398
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:23,200
Is it good?

399
00:21:27,620 --> 00:21:28,920
I suppose it's really good.

400
00:21:29,490 --> 00:21:30,490
Yes.

401
00:21:30,730 --> 00:21:31,920
Then, please excuse me.

402
00:21:32,080 --> 00:21:33,080
Of course.

403
00:21:36,270 --> 00:21:37,280
Is it good?

404
00:21:41,960 --> 00:21:42,960
Fu,

405
00:21:43,120 --> 00:21:45,900
since the work has been completed
ahead of schedule,

406
00:21:45,930 --> 00:21:47,380
the producer team said that

407
00:21:47,570 --> 00:21:49,540
we can watch the sunset around here.

408
00:21:49,580 --> 00:21:51,040
Are you interested?

409
00:21:54,770 --> 00:21:55,440
What's wrong with your eyes?

410
00:21:55,610 --> 00:21:56,610
Nothing.

411
00:21:59,690 --> 00:22:00,690
Well...

412
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:02,120
Are you in, Moo?

413
00:22:04,150 --> 00:22:05,150
Well...

414
00:22:05,500 --> 00:22:06,920
If you aren't tired yet...

415
00:22:07,630 --> 00:22:08,630
Then, sure.

416
00:22:23,300 --> 00:22:24,520
From here,

417
00:22:25,310 --> 00:22:26,510
the view is so nice, isn't it?

418
00:22:27,100 --> 00:22:28,780
While we're looking
at something like this,

419
00:22:29,310 --> 00:22:30,970
it makes us feel like

420
00:22:31,940 --> 00:22:33,710
we're just small entities, doesn't it?

421
00:22:36,980 --> 00:22:38,310
Compared to the sky,

422
00:22:39,160 --> 00:22:40,480
we're actually that small.

423
00:22:42,350 --> 00:22:44,600
Even the vast sky

424
00:22:45,820 --> 00:22:47,840
still has to shine on me.

425
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:50,000
Ouch... Ow...

426
00:22:57,880 --> 00:22:58,880
Excuse me...

427
00:22:59,240 --> 00:23:00,070
Could I jump in

428
00:23:00,220 --> 00:23:01,720
and tell you something, Fu?

429
00:23:01,960 --> 00:23:02,960
What's wrong, Ryan?

430
00:23:03,040 --> 00:23:04,460
Um...

431
00:23:04,670 --> 00:23:05,460
Well...

432
00:23:05,590 --> 00:23:08,840
My stomach is churning a bit.

433
00:23:08,960 --> 00:23:11,240
What do you mean by "a bit"?

434
00:23:11,490 --> 00:23:13,200
Oh, I mean

435
00:23:13,280 --> 00:23:14,500
if I don't rush now,

436
00:23:14,530 --> 00:23:17,680
I might become another landmark here.

437
00:23:18,640 --> 00:23:19,410
But...

438
00:23:19,570 --> 00:23:21,880
you have to go down for a while
until you find a toilet.

439
00:23:21,920 --> 00:23:22,920
Whoa.

440
00:23:23,220 --> 00:23:24,290
You can go, Ryan.

441
00:23:24,420 --> 00:23:26,246
You don't need to give me
such a detailed report.

442
00:23:26,270 --> 00:23:28,100
And don't forget
to return this to the staff.

443
00:23:28,140 --> 00:23:29,090
Yes, sir.

444
00:23:29,130 --> 00:23:33,260
So please allow me to defend
the secretary's honor first.

445
00:23:33,300 --> 00:23:34,880
Ow, it's running down my legs now.

446
00:23:36,160 --> 00:23:37,160
Ugh.

447
00:23:43,490 --> 00:23:44,490
Look there, Fu.

448
00:23:52,080 --> 00:23:53,080
So beautiful.

449
00:23:55,180 --> 00:23:56,280
Very beautiful.

450
00:23:57,710 --> 00:23:58,830
Beautiful as always.

451
00:24:03,580 --> 00:24:04,580
Beautiful as always?

452
00:24:04,840 --> 00:24:06,720
You said as if you've always been
looking at it.

453
00:24:06,910 --> 00:24:07,910
Yeah.

454
00:24:08,820 --> 00:24:10,300
I've always had my eyes on you.

455
00:24:11,590 --> 00:24:13,220
Only you.

456
00:24:14,300 --> 00:24:15,630
Haven't you felt it?

457
00:25:22,760 --> 00:25:24,150
Ryan hasn't come yet.

458
00:25:24,230 --> 00:25:25,440
I don't know if he's lost.

459
00:25:25,720 --> 00:25:27,410
Mmm... Yeah.

460
00:25:27,770 --> 00:25:28,820
I think so.

461
00:25:33,390 --> 00:25:34,390
It's thundering.

462
00:25:34,490 --> 00:25:35,490
How come?

463
00:25:36,390 --> 00:25:38,040
Moo, I think we should go

464
00:25:38,100 --> 00:25:39,410
before it rains. Let's go.

465
00:26:17,380 --> 00:26:20,000
Let's wait for the rain to ease up
before finding our way back.

466
00:26:25,180 --> 00:26:26,920
You'd better wear my jacket first.

467
00:26:27,040 --> 00:26:28,280
Take it.

468
00:26:28,340 --> 00:26:29,470
- Oh...
- You'll be cold.

469
00:26:31,330 --> 00:26:33,560
You gave me your jacket,
then what about you?

470
00:26:34,300 --> 00:26:35,390
I'm fine.

471
00:26:35,600 --> 00:26:37,110
Your shirt is so thin, see?

472
00:26:37,800 --> 00:26:39,000
Wearing mine is better.

473
00:26:39,420 --> 00:26:40,910
But you'll be cold.

474
00:26:44,240 --> 00:26:46,920
You know that I'm a cozy man.

475
00:26:47,580 --> 00:26:48,980
A little bad weather

476
00:26:50,160 --> 00:26:51,190
won't bother me at all.

477
00:26:53,210 --> 00:26:54,310
Well,

478
00:26:54,710 --> 00:26:56,210
a cozy man.

479
00:26:56,500 --> 00:26:57,880
Shaking this hard,

480
00:26:58,080 --> 00:27:00,260
when will you get cozy, Fu?

481
00:27:12,030 --> 00:27:14,800
Being this close to each other will warm us up.

482
00:27:22,620 --> 00:27:23,620
Moo...

483
00:27:23,840 --> 00:27:25,360
Won't you feel uncomfortable?

484
00:27:26,850 --> 00:27:28,490
It's better than letting you get cold.

485
00:27:29,940 --> 00:27:32,320
This can help warm us up, you know?

486
00:27:39,810 --> 00:27:41,380
When will it stop raining, huh?

487
00:27:41,420 --> 00:27:42,630
It's late now.

488
00:27:44,830 --> 00:27:46,200
I'm so sorry, Moo.

489
00:27:48,440 --> 00:27:49,640
Why did you say sorry?

490
00:27:50,330 --> 00:27:51,330
Because...

491
00:27:51,720 --> 00:27:53,620
I couldn't remember the way back,

492
00:27:54,180 --> 00:27:56,400
and I put you through this.

493
00:27:57,870 --> 00:27:58,870
That's fine.

494
00:27:59,600 --> 00:28:01,120
Ryan is about to come.

495
00:28:01,700 --> 00:28:03,030
Oh, Ryan.

496
00:28:03,550 --> 00:28:04,700
When he's back,

497
00:28:05,020 --> 00:28:06,620
I'm gonna demote him
to a security guard.

498
00:28:07,780 --> 00:28:08,780
Fu!

499
00:28:10,250 --> 00:28:12,290
I'd like to thank you, though,

500
00:28:12,430 --> 00:28:13,430
for...

501
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:15,920
taking me to watch the sunset.

502
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:18,240
That was incredible.

503
00:28:19,970 --> 00:28:22,010
Yeah, it...

504
00:28:22,860 --> 00:28:24,320
It was incredible.

505
00:30:06,040 --> 00:30:06,640
Jeab.

506
00:30:06,860 --> 00:30:08,500
- Yes.
- Your writing is better, isn't it?

507
00:30:09,510 --> 00:30:10,510
It's because...

508
00:30:10,700 --> 00:30:12,040
I put my mind to it.

509
00:30:16,650 --> 00:30:17,720
How to pronounce this?

510
00:30:18,030 --> 00:30:19,310
This reads

511
00:30:19,680 --> 00:30:20,820
"hon o yomu."

512
00:30:21,340 --> 00:30:23,090
- "Hon o..."
- It means reading books.

513
00:30:23,130 --> 00:30:24,190
I see.

514
00:30:29,130 --> 00:30:30,300
Tutoring?

515
00:30:43,070 --> 00:30:44,070
Fu.

516
00:30:46,230 --> 00:30:47,520
If you're cold, just say so.

517
00:30:48,220 --> 00:30:49,660
If you can't handle it, just say so.

518
00:30:51,720 --> 00:30:53,780
You don't need to sacrifice this much for me.

519
00:30:54,570 --> 00:30:55,680
I don't feel good at all,

520
00:30:55,710 --> 00:30:57,600
seeing you suffer for me.

521
00:31:01,100 --> 00:31:03,660
Good love is about both people giving,

522
00:31:03,800 --> 00:31:05,690
not just one person constantly receiving.

523
00:31:10,020 --> 00:31:11,020
Why are you smiling?

524
00:31:11,390 --> 00:31:12,470
Did you just...

525
00:31:16,500 --> 00:31:18,310
say "good love"?

526
00:31:20,120 --> 00:31:21,120
Uh...

527
00:31:25,100 --> 00:31:27,120
Did you see love from me

528
00:31:27,980 --> 00:31:29,500
as a good love already?

529
00:31:32,410 --> 00:31:34,210
You don't mind me anymore, right?

530
00:31:56,350 --> 00:31:57,400
Right, Fu.

531
00:31:58,060 --> 00:31:59,100
I'm curious.

532
00:31:59,910 --> 00:32:01,820
So many people approach you.

533
00:32:02,170 --> 00:32:03,660
Aren't you interested in any of them?

534
00:32:04,500 --> 00:32:05,670
Yeah, he's right!

535
00:32:06,070 --> 00:32:07,310
I was wondering the same.

536
00:32:07,970 --> 00:32:08,970
Or...

537
00:32:09,370 --> 00:32:10,576
do you already
have someone in your heart?

538
00:32:10,600 --> 00:32:12,650
Jeez, someone in my heart, my ass.

539
00:32:12,730 --> 00:32:13,730
There's no one.

540
00:32:13,990 --> 00:32:16,290
I'm happy as is,
so why bother having someone?

541
00:32:16,640 --> 00:32:18,700
But I do see that there's someone

542
00:32:18,750 --> 00:32:20,030
following you around.

543
00:32:20,230 --> 00:32:21,920
Someone... Who?

544
00:32:22,160 --> 00:32:24,430
Do you mean Moo?

545
00:32:24,490 --> 00:32:27,180
Yeah, that's him!

546
00:32:27,550 --> 00:32:30,160
He seems so simple and mid.

547
00:32:30,230 --> 00:32:32,470
It's gonna be tasteless if you date him.

548
00:32:33,210 --> 00:32:35,720
True. How's that gonna be any fun?

549
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:37,730
It's gotta be someone spicy, you know?

550
00:32:37,750 --> 00:32:39,080
- Yeah!
- Mm!

551
00:32:39,750 --> 00:32:41,800
Right, maybe Moo is just your type?

552
00:32:43,340 --> 00:32:45,400
Do you like nancy pants or something?

553
00:32:45,510 --> 00:32:46,626
Like little nancy boys and stuff!

554
00:32:46,650 --> 00:32:47,360
Hey!

555
00:32:47,590 --> 00:32:49,110
You're going too far, don't you think?

556
00:32:49,740 --> 00:32:51,110
Someone like me being into him?

557
00:32:51,630 --> 00:32:52,630
He's too wimpy.

558
00:32:53,190 --> 00:32:54,420
- Burn!
- Burn!

559
00:32:54,450 --> 00:32:56,280
You bet my type is...

560
00:32:56,310 --> 00:32:57,310
someone spicy.

561
00:32:57,440 --> 00:32:59,310
- Right on!
- That's right.

562
00:32:59,470 --> 00:33:00,470
- Though...
- Nice.

563
00:33:00,690 --> 00:33:02,530
You guys don't have to talk about him anymore.

564
00:33:03,060 --> 00:33:04,060
Let him be.

565
00:33:04,170 --> 00:33:05,570
Yeah, you're right.

566
00:33:05,890 --> 00:33:08,400
I can't even imagine Fu
being with someone so wimpy.

567
00:33:08,510 --> 00:33:10,480
How would that even work?

568
00:33:11,750 --> 00:33:12,690
Hey, let's get back to work.

569
00:33:12,720 --> 00:33:13,990
- Yeah, work.
- So fast.

570
00:33:14,890 --> 00:33:15,890
Hey, get to work.

571
00:33:23,210 --> 00:33:24,680
Someone like me being into him?

572
00:33:25,110 --> 00:33:26,110
He's too wimpy.

573
00:33:40,500 --> 00:33:41,590
So what if I am wimpy?

574
00:33:44,640 --> 00:33:46,040
Do I not have feelings if I am?

575
00:33:46,080 --> 00:33:49,560
(For Fu, from Moo-Moo)

576
00:33:51,800 --> 00:33:52,800
Just you wait.

577
00:33:54,180 --> 00:33:55,180
From now on,

578
00:33:55,350 --> 00:33:56,710
I'm not gonna be into you anymore!

579
00:34:07,300 --> 00:34:09,510
Those Chinese-looking guys
with only looks to offer...

580
00:34:11,190 --> 00:34:13,030
Don't even think
you'd ever win my heart again.

581
00:34:22,040 --> 00:34:23,040
You know,

582
00:34:24,830 --> 00:34:26,590
